          answer: "No. The school buffer is a statutory prohibition under 28-B M.R.S. §301, not a zoning standard subject to local variance. No municipality in Maine can grant a variance to allow a dispensary within the required distance of a school. If a site fails the buffer test, you must find a different site. This is one of the most important compliance checkpoints — do not sign a lease on a site that is within or too close to the buffer until you have formal written confirmation from a licensed surveyor or the municipality's GIS system."
